node.text: Always taking the road less traveled üó∫

One of the best things about being back in England for the cold winter - it actually feels like üéÖ Christmas! 
The crisp air, the blustery wind, and the frosty mornings feel far more festive than our usual sunny Christmas üéÑ days down at the beach! 
What‚Äôs your ideal Christmas weather?! Snow ‚õÑÔ∏è or sun ‚òÄÔ∏è?!

Words cannot describe how amazing it is to have Red (our bus) back in our lives üòç. Not only was she our home for just over a year, taking us on a year long road trip around Europe - she‚Äôs a member of the family! 
We‚Äôve been hitting the roads a lot since we got her back and we‚Äôre super excited to start taking you on our adventures again.

Got any questions about our European Vanlife road trip? Hit us up below. Merry Christmas üéÅüéÑüéÖ

Just because our bus is still waiting for her new engine, doesn‚Äôt mean we stop exploring! We‚Äôre in love with the cute towns in the Cotswolds. üè° What do you think? Straight out of a movie, right?!
Just posted our top things to see and do in Harz National Park blog post ‚ñ∂Ô∏è Link in Bio ‚óÄÔ∏è Comment below if you‚Äôve been and tell us your favorite thing to do in the park üöÇ üå≤

Growing up in England üè¥Û†ÅßÛ†Å¢Û†Å•Û†ÅÆÛ†ÅßÛ†Åø I never liked it. It‚Äôs cold, windy and not that pretty. However, after 5 years of full-time travel - I can safely say I was wrong. I cannot wait to explore more of England with a new set of eyes üëÄ Any suggestions on where to explore first?!
Counting the days to be back on the road üöåüí® ‚Äî what road trips do you have planned?! We‚Äôre going to explore the Cotswolds and Wales next.
Nadia fact: she‚Äôs a real life cowgirl ü§† who loves horses üê¥ what‚Äôs your sport?!
Looking back over the shots from Germany üá©üá™ we never posted. One thing we fell in love with more and more each visit was the architecture üòçüè∞ Where is your favorite architecture?!

Missing our Vanlife adventures?! Us too!

Here‚Äôs a little update. Last time you guys saw us we were in the Black Forest üå≥üçÇüå≤ and our bus had broken down. In the end we couldn‚Äôt fix it üîß and needed to rebuild the engine. We flew back to England and a few days ago (maybe you saw on our story) our beautiful bus was reunited with us in England üè¥Û†ÅßÛ†Å¢Û†Å•Û†ÅÆÛ†ÅßÛ†Åø. We decided to build a new engine over the winter period that can handle our adventures better than the OG 48hp engine and hope to have her on the road again in the next few weeks so we can show you guys the UK in winter. Expect lots of rainy üåß photos!

If you have any suggestions for where we should explore in the UK üá¨üáß, let us know! üòç
On a morning üåÖ we love opening our curtains, moving the bus into the sun and opening all the doors and windows. It makes us feel part of the forest üå≤ What‚Äôs your morning routine?
We could of stayed in Harz National Park for weeks. It‚Äôs crazy beautiful. But there‚Äôs always more to see! Which national park is your favorite?! üçÇ ‚õ∞ üçÅ

This was just what we needed. We miss America so much (planning to take our bus back to America next year) and finding this Wild West amusement park in Germany was both hilarious and gave us enough American vibes to last a bit longer. Very similar to Tombstone, AZ which we loved! ü§† üåµ üêé 
Have you ever been to Pullman City or Tombstone?
Just a muggle trying to get to Hogwarts üí´‚ú®üßô‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è
Who else is falling in love with the fall colors?! üçÅ üçÉ üçÇ

Always following the ‚òÄÔ∏è sun

We got to Germany a week ago and we‚Äôve been cruising south trying to find the sun. Now we‚Äôve found it and we couldn‚Äôt be happier. Nothing beats waking up to blue skies and exploring this beautiful world in our bus.

Do you have any recommendations for us? Where in Germany do you recommend?! üí≠
Sometimes you stumble onto the most amazing finds üòç! What‚Äôs your favorite random road-trip find?!

We spend the majority of our time free camping by beaches, lakes or mountains üòå. The occasional city visit we have is always a welcomed change of pace tho. This week Gothenburg!

I (David) studied photography üì∑ when I was in college. That entire course was based around 35mm film cameras. I even had to develop my old film (I sucked at it!) That was 11 years ago and even today my favorite camera to shoot on is my Pentax. 
What hobby do you continue to peruse in your little home on wheels? And would you like to see analog photos on our feed? ‚úåÔ∏èü§ó Have an epic weekend and keep saying yes to life! Love David and Nadia üòò
A little view into our home üè† on wheels üöå

When your backyard can literally be anything and anywhere you need to be prepared to make the most of it. That‚Äôs why our bus (the poor old girl) has been rammed with as much adventure equipment as we can fit. I mean, you‚Äôve got to be prepared, right!? üö¥üèÑüèãÔ∏èüèä Anyway‚Ä¶ who spotted David paddle boarding in the background? Leave a comment if you did! üí¨‚ù§Ô∏è

This is our happy place. Our home. 
If we‚Äôre not on some form of adventure, or taking part in all of the sports - you‚Äôll find us here. Enjoying our small but very cosy home üè† on wheels üöå

We love exploring small towns wherever we go in the world. But, there‚Äôs something particularly special about Scandinavia ‚öîÔ∏è üèî as their history and architecture is so wildly different than most cultures. 
These Stave churches are a great example of that and are always mind blowing. 
This one is in Heddal, Norway üá≥üá¥ and is the largest in the country.  It was constructed at the beginning of the 13th century. Pretty cool, huh?! Have you ever seen one before?!

The past few weeks in Norway have been the hottest üî• üòé we‚Äôve ever witnessed here. Certainly the hottest temperatures we‚Äôve had in the bus and it‚Äôs certainly throwing us out of our routines. The good thing is it‚Äôs giving us new routines. Like spending more time working our asses off and more time next to water so we can swim and a cool down. 
This weekend we decided to hit the road and explore some towns just outside of Oslo ‚õ™ 
How hot is it were you are?! ‚òÄÔ∏è ‚úåÔ∏è

Saying Yes to visiting a bucket list ‚úÖ destination!

From the beautiful countryside town of England in our last post to this small mostly car-free village üõ∂ town in north of the Netherlands. 
We were first told about this magical little town a few years back, and since then, we‚Äôve wanted to visit. Only a quick detour off of our route from England to Norway, and boy was it worth it!

There were more tourists than we expected, but upon chatting to several jolly locals, we found out that this is only the case for two months during the summer, and the rest of the time - the residents have this peaceful town all to themselves. 
In the morning, we meandered along the tiny pathways, taking in the serene beauty of Giethoorn then after a spot of lunch, we rented a boat and explored the waterways for ourselves. 
David is quite adept at boating üí™, but boy oh boy were some of our fellow visitors haphazard to say the least, it was almost as though they thought we were playing boat bumper cars - given our slow speed there‚Äôs no way to do any actual damage, and we were all laughing about one family in particular that seemed to be hitting everything in sight!

Double tap if you‚Äôve been here too ‚ù§Ô∏è

We‚Äôve been spending the last few weeks visiting family in the south east of England. Today was so hot and sunny üî• we couldn‚Äôt resist a visit to the historic town üè∞ of Rye.

We had planned on leaving a week ago, to head towards Norway via France, Belgium, The Netherlands, Germany, Denmark, and Sweden (long trip coming our way, huh!). However, we discovered that David‚Äôs passport is about to expire and have had to expend our stay, but it‚Äôs worked out well with a heat wave hitting the UK!

We love this community and how much you support our adventures, so if you‚Äôre somewhere along our route to Norway, let us know - we love to meet fellow travel junkies and vanlifers along our route. üòç‚úåÔ∏èsee you on the road!

You might not know this but Nadia is a major country girl üë©‚Äçüåæ, hailing from Yorkshire - and today used her farm charm to ask a local farmer if he knew anywhere we could camp.

So here we are in our spot for the night, the farmers field that he just finished hay timing and appreciating how kind and warm hearted people can be if you just give them a chance! üòÜ
Moments like these are why we love Vanlife. Morning drive surrounded by hot air balloons üéà in Spain üá™üá∏
We love how much of the world #vanlife allows us to see - and more importantly to us - how much of each country. Ps. Hot babe alert üòç

Not only does it have beautiful views of the town, sea, and mountains from this castle ruin but it has the most amazing cliff side spot to spend the night and everything we could ask for in the town itself. You don‚Äôt always need a plan! But now we‚Äôre here; we plan on staying a few extra days! ‚úåÔ∏è

Just stunning. üòçüèû
